Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim, peel, and cut
@Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.

== Maple Mustard Sauce ==

Place @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until
just melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), a big
pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @Pepper{pinch}. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%ounce} and stir
until evenly combined.

Place @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a second small microwave-safe bowl; microwave
until just melted, ~{30%seconds}. Add @Maple Syrup{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%tablespoon},
and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; stir until smooth.

Reserve 1 tablespoon of the mixture for brushing onto chicken in step 5.

== Potato Wedges ==

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon},
remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper.

On a separate baking sheet, toss carrots with a drizzle of olive oil, salt,
and pepper. Push carrots to one side of sheet.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
salt and pepper.

Place on opposite side of baking sheet from carrots. Evenly spread reserved
maple mustard onto tops of chicken, then mound seasoned panko on top, pressing
to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

== Roasting ==

Transfer chicken and carrots to middle rack and potatoes to top rack.

Roast until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and veggies are tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

> TIP: If chicken is done before veggies, remove from sheet and continue roasting
> veggies until browned and tender, 5-7 minutes more.

Divide chicken, potato wedges, and carrots between plates. Serve with remaining
maple mustard on the side for dipping or drizzling.